Prior to this change, the following assert fails (we end up allocating 24 bytes when we call default(T) where T is a primitive type).

```C#
long memoryBefore = GC.GetAllocatedBytesForCurrentThread();
bool startsWith = span.StartsWith<byte>(otherSpan);
long memoryAfter = GC.GetAllocatedBytesForCurrentThread();
Assert.Equal(0, memoryAfter - memoryBefore); // fails with 24 bytes
```

The default(T) check is redundant since `IsTypeComparableAsBytes` will return false when T is a reference type anyway.

